Mrs. Butterworth's is an American brand of syrups and pancake mixes owned by ConAgra Foods. The syrups come in distinctive bottles shaped in the form of a matronly woman, Mrs. Butterworth. The syrup was introduced in 1961. In 1999, the original glass bottles began appearing as plastic bottles. Mrs. Butterworth's is an American brand of syrups and pancake mixes owned by ConAgra Foods. The syrups come in distinctive bottles shaped in the form of a matronly woman, Mrs. Butterworth. The syrup was introduced in 1961. In 1999, the original glass bottles began appearing as plastic bottles. In 2019, she appeared along with an actor playing Colonel Sanders in a KFC commercial spoofing a scene from Ghost, promoting chicken and waffles using Mrs. Butterworth's syrup.